CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1941, pg. 12 reads: "National Officers, Delegates And Visitors To Debs About Town Confab In Pittsburgh" ...In the photos top, left to right; National officers: Odessa Christopher, corresponding secretary, Cleveland; Eleanor Trott, national president; Ada Fisher, Washington, Vice President; Barbara [Jones], Pittsburgh, treasurer; Lydia Taylor, National Historian; Fedelma Boyd, Cleveland, Secretary...- Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Debs About Town national officers, from left: Odessa Christopher, Eleanor Trott, Ada Fisher, Barbara Jones, Lydia Taylor, and Fedelma Boyd wearing leopard coat, posed in front of Loendi Club
